{
  "texts": [
    "A limitation of this experiment is that it does not account for contamination.",
    "If Mistral 7B's pretraining data included labeled or unlabeled parts of the datasets used here, the pretraining boost and evaluation bias may be diluted.",
    "Experiments so far passed pretraining texts independently, adding and masking pad tokens to enable batching.",
    "Packing instead combines texts into a single sequence of tokens whose length is the model's context length.",
    "Packing is often used during the initial pretraining of an LLM, where the model is trained on continuous streams of text to increase throughput (Brown et al., 2020)."
  ]
}